 <H1>Comments on Rose</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Highly modal property sheets make it hard to find and repeatedly access property widgets

</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Constant switching between mouse and keyboard

<LI>No good way to cut-and-paste multiple properties.

</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Batch code generation makes code v. model comparisons difficult

</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Diagram editing OK but somewhat clumsy

</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Text often cut-off or drawn outside of box

<LI>No alignment tools or back-to-front ordering

</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Table-of-contents widget aids users in finding individual elements, but that is all

</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Rose 98i fixes some of the most offensive usability problems of earlier versions (e.g., not being able to resize the property dialog)</H2></P>

<P></UL></P>

<P></P> 
